{
  "esm": "0.4.0",
  "metadata": {
    "name": "AlgebraicDiameterGrowth",
    "description": "Cross-binding conformance fixture (esm-sph): a single ODE coupled to TWO algebraic equations defining intermediate variables. Mirrors the diameter-growth shape that polecat nux's audit caught silently producing 1000x-wrong answers in earthsci_toolkit.simulation.simulate (escalation hq-wisp-ywi). A binding that silently drops the algebraic equations and leaves the intermediates at their default value 0 will compute dD_p/dt = 0 and produce D_p(t) ≡ D_p(0), failing every t > 0 assertion.",
    "authors": ["esm-sph conformance"],
    "tags": ["conformance", "algebraic-elimination", "dae", "esm-sph"]
  },
  "models": {
    "DiameterGrowth": {
      "reference": {
        "notes": "After algebraic elimination: G = mu*D_p = alpha*D_p, so dD_p/dt = -k*alpha*D_p (exponential decay). With k=0.1, alpha=1.0, D_p(0)=1.0 → D_p(t) = exp(-0.1*t). The mu, G defaults (1.0) satisfy the algebraic constraints at t=0, so a binding that drops the algebraic equations leaves them frozen at 1.0 and integrates dD_p/dt = -0.1 (linear decay) instead — the resulting D_p(t) = 1 - 0.1*t diverges sharply from the exponential at every t > 0."
      },
      "variables": {
        "D_p": {
          "type": "state",
          "units": "1",
          "default": 1.0,
          "description": "Particle-diameter-shaped state variable."
        },
        "mu": {
          "type": "state",
          "units": "1",
          "default": 1.0,
          "description": "Algebraic intermediate (= alpha). Default chosen to satisfy the algebraic constraint at t=0; bindings that drop the algebraic equations leave it pinned at 1.0 and make D_p decay linearly instead of exponentially."
        },
        "G": {
          "type": "state",
          "units": "1",
          "default": 1.0,
          "description": "Algebraic intermediate (= mu * D_p). Same rationale as mu."
        },
        "k": {"type": "parameter", "default": 0.1},
        "alpha": {"type": "parameter", "default": 1.0}
      },
      "equations": [
        {
          "lhs": {"op": "D", "args": ["D_p"], "wrt": "t"},
          "rhs": {"op": "*", "args": [{"op": "-", "args": ["k"]}, "G"]}
        },
        {
          "lhs": "G",
          "rhs": {"op": "*", "args": ["mu", "D_p"]}
        },
        {
          "lhs": "mu",
          "rhs": "alpha"
        }
      ],
      "tolerance": {"rel": 1.0e-6, "abs": 1.0e-10},
      "tests": [
        {
          "id": "diameter_growth_algebraic_elimination",
          "description": "D_p(t) = exp(-0.1*t); mu(t) = 1.0; G(t) = exp(-0.1*t). Assertions on all three catch silent algebraic-elimination failures whether the runner reads states only or also probes algebraic intermediates.",
          "initial_conditions": {"D_p": 1.0},
          "parameter_overrides": {"k": 0.1, "alpha": 1.0},
          "time_span": {"start": 0.0, "end": 10.0},
          "assertions": [
            {"variable": "D_p", "time": 0.0,  "expected": 1.0},
            {"variable": "D_p", "time": 1.0,  "expected": 0.9048374180359595},
            {"variable": "D_p", "time": 5.0,  "expected": 0.6065306597126334},
            {"variable": "D_p", "time": 10.0, "expected": 0.36787944117144233}
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  }
}
